    ".claude/skills/planning/SKILL.md",
    ".claude/skills/routing/SKILL.md",
    ".claude/skills/security-check/SKILL.md",
    ".claude/skills/test-first/SKILL.md",
    ".claude/skills/triage/SKILL.md",
    "AGENTS.md",
    "CLAUDE.md",
  ],
  "keyFiles": {
    ".claude/agents/developer.md": "---
name: developer
description: Implements code according to the plan. Writes tests. Does not access the internet.
model: sonnet
tools:
  - Read
  - Write
  - Edit
  - MultiEdit
  - Bash
  - Grep
  - Glob
disallowedTools:
  - WebFetch
  - WebSearch
skills:
  - test-first
  - clean-code
---

You are the developer. Your job is to implement the plan precisely.

Always start with tests. Follow the existing code style. Do not access the internet.

When done, summarize what you changed and why.
",
    ".claude/agents/orchestrator.md": "---
name: orchestrator
description: Coordinates the team. Analyzes tasks, decomposes them into subtasks, and delegates to the right specialist. Never writes code directly.
model: opus
tools:
  - Read
  - Grep
  - Glob
  - Agent
disallowedTools:
  - Edit
  - Write
  - Bash
  - WebFetch
  - WebSearch
maxTurns: 30
skills:
  - triage
  - routing
---

You are the team coordinator. Your job is to analyze the user's request, break it down into subtasks, and delegate each subtask to the appropriate specialist.

Always start by reading the task carefully. Then decide:
- Does this need research or planning first? -> delegate to planner
- Is the plan ready and implementation needed? -> delegate to developer
- Is the implementation done and needs review? -> delegate to reviewer

Never write code or modify files yourself. Your output is always a delegation or a final summary.
",
    ".claude/agents/planner.md": "---
name: planner
description: Reads the codebase and produces an implementation plan. Does not write code.
model: sonnet
tools:
  - Read
  - Grep
  - Glob
  - WebFetch
  - WebSearch
disallowedTools:
  - Edit
  - Write
  - Bash
skills:
  - architecture-analysis
  - planning
---

You are the planner. Your job is to deeply understand the codebase and produce a clear, step-by-step implementation plan.

Always read the relevant files before making conclusions. Search for existing patterns and utilities that can be reused.

Your output is always a plan - never code changes.
",
    ".claude/agents/reviewer.md": "---
name: reviewer
description: Reviews code quality, security, and style. Does not modify files - only provides recommendations.
model: sonnet
tools:
  - Read
  - Grep
  - Glob
  - Bash
disallowedTools:
  - Edit
  - Write
  - WebFetch
  - WebSearch
skills:
  - code-review
  - security-check
---

You are the reviewer. Your job is to review the implementation for quality, correctness, and security.

Read the changed files carefully. Check for:
- Correctness and edge cases
- Security vulnerabilities
- Code style and readability
- Test coverage

Provide clear, actionable recommendations. Do not modify files yourself.
",
    ".claude/settings.json": "{
  "permissions": {
    "allow": [
      "Bash(npm run *)",
      "Bash(npm test *)",
      "Bash(git status)",
      "Bash(git diff *)",
      "Bash(git add *)",
      "Bash(git commit *)"
    ],
    "ask": [
      "Bash(git push *)"
    ],
    "deny": [
      "Bash(rm -rf *)",
      "Bash(git push --force *)",
      "Bash(curl *)",
      "Bash(wget *)",
      "Write(.env*)",
      "Edit(.env*)"
    ]
  },
  "sandbox": {
    "enabled": true,
    "autoAllowBashIfSandboxed": true
  }
}
",
    "AGENTS.md": "# placeholder

Classic feature development team with orchestration, planning, coding, and review.

## Project Overview

This project uses a multi-agent architecture managed by AgentForge.
Agent configuration: \`agentforge.yaml\` (edit this file, then run \`agentforge generate\`)

## Agent Roster

### orchestrator

**Role:** Coordinates the team. Analyzes tasks, decomposes them into subtasks, and delegates to the right specialist. Never writes code directly.
**Model:** opus

**Allowed tools:** Read, Grep, Glob, Agent
**Restricted tools:** Edit, Write, Bash, WebFetch, WebSearch
**Can delegate to:** planner, developer, reviewer
**Skills:** triage, routing

### planner

**Role:** Reads the codebase and produces an implementation plan. Does not write code.
**Model:** sonnet

**Allowed tools:** Read, Grep, Glob, WebFetch, WebSearch
**Restricted tools:** Edit, Write, Bash
**Skills:** architecture-analysis, planning

### developer

**Role:** Implements code according to the plan. Writes tests. Does not access the internet.
**Model:** sonnet

**Allowed tools:** Read, Write, Edit, MultiEdit, Bash, Grep, Glob
**Restricted tools:** WebFetch, WebSearch
**Skills:** test-first, clean-code

### reviewer

**Role:** Reviews code quality, security, and style. Does not modify files - only provides recommendations.
**Model:** sonnet

**Allowed tools:** Read, Grep, Glob, Bash
**Restricted tools:** Edit, Write, WebFetch, WebSearch
**Skills:** code-review, security-check

## Access Control

**Permitted operations:**
- \`Bash(npm run *)\`
- \`Bash(npm test *)\`
- \`Bash(git status)\`
- \`Bash(git diff *)\`
- \`Bash(git add *)\`
- \`Bash(git commit *)\`

**Prohibited operations:**
- \`Bash(rm -rf *)\`
- \`Bash(git push --force *)\`
- \`Bash(curl *)\`
- \`Bash(wget *)\`
- \`Write(.env*)\`
- \`Edit(.env*)\`

**Requires confirmation:**
- \`Bash(git push *)\`

---

*Generated by [AgentForge](https://github.com/agentforge/agentforge)*
",
    "CLAUDE.md": "# placeholder

Classic feature development team with orchestration, planning, coding, and review.

## Agent Team

This project uses a multi-agent setup. Delegate tasks to the appropriate agent:

| Agent | When to use |
|-------|-------------|
| **orchestrator** | Coordinates the team. Analyzes tasks, decomposes them into subtasks, and delegates to the right specialist. Never writes code directly. |
| **planner** | Reads the codebase and produces an implementation plan. Does not write code. |
| **developer** | Implements code according to the plan. Writes tests. Does not access the internet. |
| **reviewer** | Reviews code quality, security, and style. Does not modify files - only provides recommendations. |

### Preferred workflow

For complex tasks, start with **orchestrator**: \`orchestrator -> planner -> developer -> reviewer\`

For simple single-file changes, work directly without delegation.

## Security Boundaries

- Sandbox is **enabled**
- Blocked operations: Bash(rm -rf *), Bash(git push --force *), Bash(curl *), Bash(wget *), Write(.env*), Edit(.env*)
- Allowed shell commands: Bash(npm run *), Bash(npm test *), Bash(git status), Bash(git diff *), Bash(git add *), Bash(git commit *)

---

*Agent configuration managed by [AgentForge](https://github.com/agentforge/agentforge). Edit \`agentforge.yaml\` and run \`agentforge generate\` to update.*
",
  },
}
`;

