Research-first team. Researcher has full internet access; developer does not.

## Project Overview

This project uses a multi-agent architecture managed by AgentForge.
Agent configuration: \`agentforge.yaml\` (edit this file, then run \`agentforge generate\`)

## Agent Roster

### orchestrator

**Role:** Coordinates research and implementation. Delegates research tasks to the researcher and coding tasks to the developer.
**Model:** opus

**Allowed tools:** Read, Grep, Glob, Agent
**Restricted tools:** Edit, Write, Bash, WebFetch, WebSearch
**Can delegate to:** researcher, planner, developer

### researcher

**Role:** Finds information in documentation and on the web. Produces research reports and source summaries.
**Model:** haiku

**Allowed tools:** Read, Grep, Glob, WebFetch, WebSearch
**Restricted tools:** Edit, Write, Bash
**Skills:** research-report, source-validation

### planner

**Role:** Analyzes the codebase and research findings to produce an implementation plan.
**Model:** sonnet

**Allowed tools:** Read, Grep, Glob
**Restricted tools:** Edit, Write, Bash, WebFetch, WebSearch
**Skills:** architecture-analysis, planning

### developer

**Role:** Implements code according to the plan. No internet access - all needed information must come from the planner or researcher.
**Model:** sonnet

**Allowed tools:** Read, Write, Edit, MultiEdit, Bash, Grep, Glob
**Restricted tools:** WebFetch, WebSearch
**Skills:** test-first, clean-code

